---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: "help_output(& [\"git\", \"vaccinate\", \"--help\"])"
---
Add R/Python/editor junk patterns to the global git ignore

Appends the lab's ignore patterns (R/Python/editor droppings) to your global git ignore so they are never committed to any repo. Pass --project to write to this repo's .gitignore instead.

Usage: hpds git vaccinate [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --project
          Append to this repo's .gitignore instead of the global git ignore

  -v, --verbose
          Show more detail (underlying commands, tool names)

  -q, --quiet
          Suppress all output except errors

      --no-color
          Disable colored output

      --config <PATH>
          Use this config file instead of discovering hpds.toml

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
